index 0000000..f84753d
--- /dev/null
+++ b/CONTRIBUTING.md
@@ -0,0 +1,118 @@
+# Contributing to Wyrd
+
+Thanks for your interest in Wyrd! Contributions are welcome. This guide covers
+the few rules our CI enforces so you don't learn them by tripping a red check.
+
+Before getting involved, please also read the
+[Code of Conduct](docs/governance/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) and
+[Governance](docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md). Architecture, specifications, and
+decision records live under [`docs/design/`](docs/design/README.md) — **start
+there** to understand how Wyrd is built and why.
+
+## The three rules CI enforces
+
+Every pull request runs these checks. Each one corresponds to a workflow under
+[`.github/workflows/`](.github/workflows) and reports a status, so a PR that
+follows the rules below goes green on the first try.
+
+### 1. Sign off every commit (DCO)
+
+Wyrd tracks contribution provenance with the
+[Developer Certificate of Origin](https://developercertificate.org/) (DCO), not
+a CLA — see [ADR-0003 §1](docs/design/adr/0003-apache-2-license-and-dco.md).
+**Every commit** must carry a `Signed-off-by:` trailer certifying you have the
+right to submit it under Wyrd's Apache-2.0 license. The easiest way is the `-s`
+flag:
+
+```sh
+git commit -s -m "your message"
+```
+
+This appends a line like `Signed-off-by: Your Name <you@example.com>` using your
+configured `user.name` and `user.email`. The `dco` workflow
+([`.github/workflows/dco.yml`](.github/workflows/dco.yml)) checks **every** commit
+in the PR — including docs-only ones — and fails if any is missing the trailer.
+If you forgot, add the sign-off and re-push; the check re-runs on each push:
+
+```sh
+# fix the most recent commit
+git commit --amend -s --no-edit && git push --force-with-lease
+
+# or sign off a range of commits
+git rebase --signoff origin/main && git push --force-with-lease
+```
+
+### 2. Link a real issue
+
+Every PR must reference a real, existing issue (not another PR) for
+traceability. The `require-issue` workflow
+([`.github/workflows/require-issue.yml`](.github/workflows/require-issue.yml))
+scans the PR **title or body** for an issue reference and confirms the number
+resolves to an actual issue in this repository.
+
+Put a closing keyword in the PR description so the issue auto-closes on merge:
+
+```
+Closes #123
+```
+
+`Fixes #123`, `Refs #123`, a bare `#123`, or a full issue URL all satisfy the
+check. No issue yet? [Open one first](https://github.com/getwyrd/wyrd/issues/new/choose)
+— a bug report or enhancement template will guide you. The check re-runs when you
+edit the PR, so adding the reference after opening clears it.
+
+### 3. Pass the Rust gate
+
+For any change touching Rust (the gate is skipped for docs-only and Markdown
+changes), run the full gate **before pushing**:
+
+```sh
+cargo xtask ci
+```
+
+This is the single source of gate truth (ADR-0016): the same command runs on
+your laptop and in CI ([`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](.github/workflows/ci.yml)),
+so a green local run means a green PR. It runs, in order:
+
+- `cargo fmt --check` — formatting,
+- `cargo clippy -D warnings` — lints (warnings are errors),
+- `cargo build` — the workspace,
+- `cargo test` — the unit, integration, and deterministic-simulation (DST)
+  tests (ADR-0009),
+- `cargo deny check` — dependency licenses and advisories
+  ([`deny.toml`](deny.toml), ADR-0003 §2),
+- the on-disk-format **conformance vectors** (ADR-0002).
+
+If `cargo xtask ci` is green, your PR's Rust gate will be too.
+
+## Optional: the Tier-2 integration tier
+
+A heavier, container-based tier stands up a cluster of real, networked gRPC
+servers under docker-compose and runs the end-to-end write/read test against them
+(Milestone 2, proposal 0004). It is **not** part of `cargo xtask ci` and **not** a
+required PR check — it runs nightly for post-merge regression visibility
+([`.github/workflows/integration-nightly.yml`](.github/workflows/integration-nightly.yml)).
+
+If your change affects the networked data path, run it locally. It needs a Docker
+runtime with the compose plugin:
+
+```sh
+cargo xtask integration
+```
+
+Without Docker it is skipped locally (and is a hard failure only in the nightly
+CI job, where Docker is guaranteed).
+
+## Submitting a pull request
+
+1. [Open or find an issue](https://github.com/getwyrd/wyrd/issues) describing the
+   change.
+2. Create a branch and make your change, committing with `git commit -s`.
+3. Run `cargo xtask ci` (and `cargo xtask integration` if the data path is
+   affected).
+4. Open a PR. The
+   [pull-request template](.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) pre-seeds a
+   `Closes #N` line and a checklist for the rules above.
+
+A maintainer will review per [Governance](docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md). Thanks
+for contributing!
